```

## Determinism evidence
- v1 = first line only (`head -n 1`); v2 = first line + `[N words]`. Per-doc byte lengths: alpha 52→63, beta 67→78, gamma 60→71 — v2 strictly longer by exactly 11 bytes in every case. Invariant is structural (v2 = v1 + a non-empty `[N words]\n` line), holds even for single-line / no-trailing-newline / empty docs (verified on /tmp copies during review).
- Judge decides purely by `wc -c`; etude's per-pair presentation swap is reversed by mapWinnerBack, so the canonical winner is position-invariant. Bench reproduced B=3 A=0 tie=0 across seeds 0/1/2/7/42/99.

## Isolation
Throwaway `git init` repo + single EXIT trap removing WORK always and BINDIR only when built locally. No writes to the real repo or its refs/etude/*. Temp-dir leak check after run: delta 0.

## Result: PASS
All checks green; determinism and isolation empirically confirmed.
